    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="923"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d923">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00110 E.W./9–444</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Soviet Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gromyko</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-04">September 4,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: The Soviet Government has taken
                    note of the memorandum sent to the Embassy on August 24, 1944, by the Department
                    of State,<note n="26" xml:id="d923fn26">See footnote 5, <ref target="#pg_1412"
                            >p. 1412</ref>.</note> and also of the enclosed paraphrase of your
                    telegram sent to the American Minister in Bern, in which you give him
                    instructions regarding the necessity of making representations to the Swiss
                    Government on the question of the non-admission into neutral countries of the
                    leaders of the Axis Powers and their adherents.</p>
                <p>I am happy to inform you that the Soviet Government shares the views of the
                    Government of the United States of America on this question.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>[For the] Ambassador<lb/>[Signature illegible]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
